Object.Name: Control unit cycle time (TNcyc)
Object.Comment: The control unit cycle time defines the cyclic intervals during which the control unit generates new command values. It is defined as 62us (only for one channel devices), 125us, 250us, ..., up to 20ms in steps of 250us. Control unit cycle time and communication cycle time (S-0-0002) should be set to the same value. The control unit cycle time must be greater or equal than the position control cycle time (P-0-0004) if the operation mode position control is used. Interpolation modes can be configured (P-0-0556) to generate the additional position commands in case of a lower position control cycle time.

Object.Name: Communication cycle time (tSync)
Object.Comment: The communication cycle time of the interface defines the intervals during which the cyclic data are transferred via EtherCAT. It is defined as 62us (only for one channel devices), 125us, 250us, ..., up to 20ms in steps of 250us. Communication cycle time and control unit cycle time (S-0-0001) should be set to the same value.

Object.Name: Feedback acquisition capture point (t4)
Object.Comment: The feedback capture latch is always synchronized with the EtherCAT distributed clock (DC) synchronization signal Sync 1. It can be adjusted by the TwinCAT System Manager

Object.Name: Class 1 diagnostic (C1D)
Object.Comment: Drive shut-down error. A drive error situation of class C1D leads to the following: A best case deceleration followed by torque/force release at nmin. The drive shut-down error bit for C1D is set to '1' in the drive status (bit 13). The error bit is reset to '0' by the drive only when no errors of C1D exists and after the command 'reset class 1 diagnostic' (IDN S-0-0099) has been received by the drive.

Object.Name: Class 2 diagnostic (C2D)
Object.Comment: Shut-down warning (warning). When a warning is activated or canceled in the C2D, this sets the change bit for C2D in the drive status (bit 12) to a binary 1. When the C2D is read via the parameter channel, the C2D change bit is canceled and reset to 0.

Object.Name: Velocity command value
Object.Comment: During operating mode velocity control, the control unit provides the velocity command values to the drive updated with the control unit cycle time. Scaling is constant: Rotary motor: 1 rpm corresponds to 2^30 / 60000 counts (17895.697). Linear motor: 1 m/s corresponds to 2^30 / 24 counts (at 24 mm pole pitch)

Object.Name: Additive velocity command value
Object.Comment: The additive velocity command value is an additional velocity command value which is added to the velocity command value (S-0-0036). The additive velocity command value can be used by the controller as velocity feed forward signal.

Object.Name: Velocity feedback 1 value
Object.Comment: The velocity feedback 1 value can be transferred from the drive to the control unit. The velocity feedback 1 value refers to the motor feedback. In case of using the observer the observed velocity is provided. Scaling see S-0-0036.

Object.Name: Velocity polarity parameter
Object.Comment: This parameter is used to configure polarities of velocity data for specific applications. Polarities are not changed drive internal. Only the interface (input and output signals) is affected. The motor shaft turns clockwise when there is a positive velocity command and no inversion is programmed.

Object.Name: Velocity data scaling type
Object.Comment: The scaling of the drive controller's velocity data is not adjustable. The controller always reads 2 which stands for rotary scaling.

Object.Name: Velocity data scaling factor
Object.Comment: This parameter provides the scaling factor of the velocity data interface. The velocity data scaling is not changeable and is set to the following scaling: 1 Revolutions/min = 1 rpm = 17895.69707 (= 2^30 / 60000) 1 least significant bit (lsb) = 55879.35448e-9 Revolution/min (=60000/2^30) The value 55879 is provided for the control unit.

Object.Name: Velocity data scaling exponent
Object.Comment: This parameter provides the scaling exponent of the velocity interface data. The velocity data scaling is not changeable. See S-0-0045. 1 least significant bit (lsb) = 55879.35448e-9 Revolutions/min (=60000/2^30) The value -9 is provided for the control unit.

Object.Name: Position command value
Object.Comment: During the position control drive operation mode, the position command values are transferred from the control unit to the drive according to the time pattern of the control unit cycle.

Object.Name: Additive position command value
Object.Comment: This IDN is used if an additional position offset is required during position control operation mode in the drive. The additive position command ofset is added to the position command value (IDN S-0-0047).

Object.Name: Position feedback 1 value (motor feedback)
Object.Comment: The position feedback 1 value (motor feedback) displays the actual position of the motor feedback.

Object.Name: Position feedback 2 value (external feedback)
Object.Comment: The position feedback 2 value (additional feedback) displays the actual position of the second feedback.

Object.Name: Position polarity parameters
Object.Comment: This parameter is used to switch polarities of reported position data for specific applications. Polarities are switched outside (i.e., on the input and output) of a closed loop system. The motor shaft turns clockwise (as viewed from the output shaft) when there is a positive position command difference and no inversion is programmed.

Object.Name: Position data scaling type
Object.Comment: A variety of scaling methods can be selected by means of the scaling type parameter.

Object.Name: Position resolution
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the position resolution of the 32-bit position data of the drive interface. It specifies the number of increments per turn (360°) for rotary motors. The LSB of the position data thus has a weighting of 360° / S-0-0079. For linear motors it specifies the number of increments per pole pitch (e.g. 24 mm). The LSB of the position data thus has a weighting of 24 mm / S-0-0079. The position resolution can be configured between 2^20 increments per turn (=1 048 576 inc per turn or pole pitch) and 2^30 (=1 073 741 824 inc per turn or pole pitch). Increasing the resolution is also decreasing the number of countable turns. In case off using feedback 2 in combination with a gear the effective resolution of the load can be calculated by S-0-0079 x P-0-0182 / P-0-0183.

Object.Name: Feedback 1 type
Object.Comment: This parameter structure defines the feedback 1 type. Feedback 1 is the primary motor feedback and is also used to calculate the commutation position.

Object.Name: Scanned feedback 1 type
Object.Comment: This read only parameter structure displays the feedback 1 data which are read from the feedback during the execution of P-0-0163 "Scan feedback 1 (pc)".

Object.Name: Feedback 1 gear numerator
Object.Comment: Feedback 1 gear numerator is usually set to 1 because in most motors is no gear between motor and feedback 1.

Object.Name: Feedback 1 gear denominator
Object.Comment: Feedback 1 gear denominator is usually set to 1 because in most motors is no gear between motor and feedback 1.

Object.Name: Feedback 1 reference signal
Object.Comment: Select the reference source of the feedback system and adjust the compare voltage level. The compare voltage can be set in a range of -570mV up to 570mV.

Object.Name: Feedback 1 identification
Object.Comment: This string with up to 64 byte is stored in the nonvolatile memory of feedback 1. The string is stored in the feedback memory if the procedure command P-0-0158 "Save feedback 1 identification (pc)" is executed and read from the feedback during the power up sequence of the feedback.

Object.Name: Save feedback 1 identification (pc)
Object.Comment: Save the feedback identification to encoder nonvolatile memory.

Object.Name: Raw position feedback 1 value
Object.Comment: The raw position feedback 1 value displays the actual position of the motor feedback without any offset and without modulo calculation.

Object.Name: Calibrate commutation offset (pc)
Object.Comment: With this procedure command (pc) the required mechanical commutation offset of the motor can be adjusted. Be careful: This command may cause a movement of the motor. The resulting offset value can be read via P-0-0058 (Mechanical commutation offset).

Object.Name: Feedback 1: Save commutation offset (pc)
Object.Comment: Feedback 1: The commutation offset is saved in the feedback memory.

Object.Name: Feedback 1: Save digital name plate (pc)
Object.Comment: Feedback 1: The digital name plate is saved in the feedback memory.

Object.Name: Scan feedback 1 (pc)
Object.Comment: This procedure command detects the connected feedback 1. The results are displayed in P-0-0151 "Scanned feedback 1 type".

Object.Name: Commutation offset calibration parameter
Object.Comment: This parameters are used by the procedure command P-0-0160 "Calibrate commutation offset".

Object.Name: Motor and feedback connection check (pc)
Object.Comment: This procedure command can be used to inject a defined (P-0-167) current vector to check commutation and rotation direction.

Object.Name: Motor and feedback connection check parameter
Object.Comment: This IDN contains parameters to check commutation and rotation direction (P-0-166).

Object.Name: Actual resolver data
Object.Comment: This parameter displays some actual data of the connected resolver.

Object.Name: Feedback status
Object.Comment: This parameter displays some actual data of the connected encoder.

Object.Name: Feedback data state
Object.Comment: This read only parameter displays the data state flags of the feedback 1 and 2 position.

Object.Name: Feedback 2 type
Object.Comment: This parameter structure defines the feedback 2 type. Feedback 2 is the secondary feedback connected to the load side and used in the position control loop if a appropriate operation mode is selected.

Object.Name: Scanned feedback 2 type
Object.Comment: This read only parameter structure displays the feedback 2 data which are read from the feedback during the execution of P-0-0193 "Scan feedback 2 (pc)".

Object.Name: Feedback 2 gear numerator
Object.Comment: If a gear is placed between motor and load / feedback 2 the ratio is described by numerator and denominator (P-0-0183). Usually the numerator is larger than the denominator (load is slower).

Object.Name: Feedback 2 gear denominator
Object.Comment: If a gear is placed between motor and load / feedback 2 the ratio is described by numerator (P-0-0182) and denominator. Usually the numerator is larger than the denominator (load is slower).

Object.Name: Feedback 2 reference signal
Object.Comment: Select the reference source of the feedback 2 system and adjust the compare voltage level. The compare voltage can be set in a range of -570mV up to 570mV.

Object.Name: Feedback 2 identification
Object.Comment: This string with up to 64 byte is stored in the nonvolatile memory of feedback 2. The string is stored in the feedback memory if the procedure command P-0-0188 "Save feedback 2 identification (pc)" is executed and read from the feedback during the power up sequence of the feedback.

Object.Name: Save feedback 2 identification (pc)
Object.Comment: Save the feedback identification to encoder nonvolatile memory.

Object.Name: Raw position feedback 2 value
Object.Comment: The raw position feedback 2 value displays the actual position of the additional feedback without any offset and without modulo calculation.

Object.Name: Position feedback 1 value (64 bit)
Object.Comment: The position feedback 1 value (64 bit) displays the actual position of the motor feedback as 64 bit value. In case of a rotational feedback the singleturnposition is displayed in the low DWORD and the turns are dislayed in the high DWORD.

Object.Name: Position feedback 2 value (64 bit)
Object.Comment: The position feedback 2 value (64 bit) displays the actual position of the additional feedback as 64 bit value. In case of a rotational feedback the singleturnposition is displayed in the low DWORD and the turns are dislayed in the high DWORD.

Object.Name: Feedback 2: Save digital name plate (pc)
Object.Comment: Feedback 2: The digital name plate is saved in the feedback memory.

Object.Name: Scan feedback 2 (pc)
Object.Comment: This procedure command detects the connected feedback 2. The results are displayed in P-0-0181 "Scanned feedback 2 type".

Object.Name: Velocity observer

Object.Name: Velocity controller positive output limit
Object.Comment: The configurable positive output limit value limits the velocity controller output (torque command) in the positive direction of rotation. Scaling is according to P-0-0094.

Object.Name: Velocity controller negative output limit
Object.Comment: The configurable negative output limit value limits the velocity controller output (torque command) in the negative direction of rotation. Scaling is according to P-0-0094.

Object.Name: Active load damping
Object.Comment: Systems using a high resolution 2nd feedback can use active load damping to improve the velocity control performance in case of compliantly coupled load.

Object.Name: Position controller control word
Object.Comment: This parameter displays the internal control word of the position controller and can be used for diagnostic purposes.

Object.Name: Position controller status word
Object.Comment: This parameter displays the internal state of the position controller and can be used for diagnostic purposes.

Object.Name: Effective position command value
Object.Comment: This IDN provides the position command value generated by the optional interpolator.

Object.Name: Position command value monitoring window
Object.Comment: If a sequence of cyclic transferred position command values (S-0-0047) is showing an impracticable jump the error F324 is reported. The position difference between two samples corresponds to the requested velocity. The monitoring window scaling is configured in percent of S-0-0091 'Bipolar velocity limit'.

Object.Name: Position interpolation type
Object.Comment: In configurations where the position control loop update time (P-0-0004) is faster than the communication cycle time (S-0-0002) the internal fine-interpolation type can be configured to linear- (0) or cubic-interpolation (1).

Object.Name: Acceleration feed forward filter time constant
Object.Comment: A first order lag can be utilized to filter the internal calculated acceleration feed forward signal.

Object.Comment: This IDN delivers the velocity command from the position controller before adding any feed forward.

Object.Comment: The position loop following error at constant speed can be reduced by using the calculated velocity feed forward signal.

Object.Name: Bipolar position controller output limitation
Object.Comment: The bipolar position controller output limit value describes the maximum allowable position controller output (actuating velocity) in both directions.

Object.Name: Feedforward velocity time shift
Object.Comment: Time shift of the velocity feedforwared value. If the time value is greater as zero the feedforward value is leading.

Object.Name: Torque/force command value (Dynamic MDT)
Object.Comment: During operation mode torque/force control, torque/force command values are transferred from the control unit to the drive updated with the control unit cycle time. The value is related to the configured channel peak torque/force (P-0-0094). 1000 (=100.0%) requests the maximal value.

Object.Name: Velocity command value (Dynamic MDT)
Object.Comment: During operating mode velocity control, the control unit provides the velocity command values to the drive updated with the control unit cycle time. Scaling is constant: Rotary motor: 1 rpm corresponds to 2^30 / 60000 counts (17895.697). Linear motor: 1 m/s corresponds to 2^30 / 24 counts (at 24 mm pole pitch)

Object.Name: Position command value (Dynamic MDT)
Object.Comment: During the position control drive operation mode, the position command values are transferred from the control unit to the drive according to the time pattern of the control unit cycle. The modulo calculation isn't considered here.
